20:35.670 --> 20:38.055
Oh, give me that old time religion

20:38.055 --> 20:40.174
Give me that old time religion

20:40.675 --> 20:41.676
Give me that old time religion

20:42.176 --> 20:44.178
You're the stranger, ain't you

20:44.178 --> 20:47.682
are you looking for a nice, clean place to stay

20:47.682 --> 20:50.685
I had a nice, clean place to stay, madam,

20:50.685 --> 20:53.187
and I left it to come here.

20:53.688 --> 20:55.189
If it's good enough for Brady

20:55.189 --> 20:57.692
If it's good enough for Brady

20:57.692 --> 20:59.694
if it's good enough for Brady

20:59.694 --> 21:02.196
then it's good enough for me

21:03.197 --> 21:05.616
[Playing organ]

21:24.635 --> 21:25.636
Rachel.

21:32.143 --> 21:34.645
I waited supper for you.
it's on the table

21:45.656 --> 21:48.159
peace will come, my daughter.

21:48.159 --> 21:49.660
God we must thank

21:49.660 --> 21:51.662
that the sinner stands naked and exposed.

21:52.163 --> 21:53.664
Stop preaching, Pa.

21:53.664 --> 21:54.665
I have something to tell you.

21:54.665 --> 21:56.167
You're upset, daughter.

21:56.667 --> 21:57.668
Eat something and we'll talk in the morning.

21:57.668 --> 22:01.172
No. Now. I'm not leaving Bert.

22:03.674 --> 22:06.177
I don't understand.

22:06.177 --> 22:08.179
You heard what Mr. Brady said

22:08.179 --> 22:10.681
I love him, Pa. I love him.

22:10.681 --> 22:13.184
No, no. that is the love of Judas.

22:13.184 --> 22:15.186
This man has nothing to offer you but sin.

22:15.186 --> 22:17.188
I told you that from the beginning.

22:17.188 --> 22:18.189
what's he done

22:18.689 --> 22:20.191
what's he done that's so terrible

22:20.191 --> 22:22.693
Why do you hate him so

22:23.194 --> 22:27.198
Because I love god, and I hate his enemies.

22:27.698 --> 22:28.699
Bert loves God.

22:28.699 --> 22:31.202
Then what is he doing with Henry Drummond

22:31.702 --> 22:33.704
Why is he bringing Henry Drummond here

22:33.704 --> 22:38.209
to spew his atheistic filth into the ears of our people

22:38.209 --> 22:39.710
You're a schoolteacher.

22:39.710 --> 22:43.214
You know how easy it is to mold
minds for good

22:43.214 --> 22:44.715
or to twist them for evil.

22:44.715 --> 22:46.217
Bert didn't twist any minds.

22:46.217 --> 22:48.719
You're infected with the poison of his agnosticism.

22:48.719 --> 22:50.721
Now get down on your knees and pray for forgiveness.

22:51.222 --> 22:52.223
Forgiveness for what

22:52.223 --> 22:53.724
Because you have betrayed me.

22:53.724 --> 22:54.725
You have betrayed your faith.

22:54.725 --> 22:56.727
I'm not betraying anybody.

22:58.229 --> 22:59.730
I'm glad your mother isn't here

22:59.730 --> 23:01.232
to see what's become of you.

23:01.232 --> 23:02.233
Pa, please listen to me.

23:02.733 --> 23:04.735
If she is looking down from heaven,

23:04.735 --> 23:09.240
I ask her to forgive you and to forgive me.

23:09.240 --> 23:11.742
Pa, ever since I was a little girl,

23:11.742 --> 23:13.744
I'd wake up in the middle of the night

23:13.744 --> 23:15.246
afraid of the dark,

23:15.246 --> 23:17.248
like the house was upside down,

23:17.248 --> 23:18.749
and if I didn't hang onto the Mattress,

23:19.250 --> 23:21.752
I'd fall out into the sky--

23:21.752 --> 23:23.254
Forgive her, Mother,

23:23.254 --> 23:24.755
Forgive her, dear God...

23:24.755 --> 23:26.257
I wanted to run to you,

23:26.257 --> 23:28.259
to have you tell me that I was safe,

23:28.259 --> 23:30.261
that everything was all right,

23:30.261 --> 23:33.264
but I was always more afraid of you than of falling.

23:33.264 --> 23:35.266
It's the same way now.

23:35.266 --> 23:36.767
I have failed.

23:40.271 --> 23:42.273
Tell me what to do, dear lord.

23:42.273 --> 23:43.774
Guide my faltering steps.

23:43.774 --> 23:44.775
Pa. Pa.

23:45.276 --> 23:46.777
I love my daughter. how can I save her

23:47.278 --> 23:49.280
Pa, get up. Please get up.

23:49.280 --> 23:51.282
And I will sprinkle clean water upon you,

23:51.782 --> 23:53.784
and you shall be clean.

23:53.784 --> 23:56.287
From all your filthiness and from your idols

23:56.287 --> 23:58.289
Will I cleanse you

23:58.289 --> 24:00.791
and a new heart also will I give you

24:00.791 --> 24:03.294
and a new spirit put within you,

24:03.794 --> 24:08.299
and I will tear out the stony heart of flesh,

24:08.299 --> 24:11.802
and I will give you a heart of flesh.

24:11.802 --> 24:13.304
[Sobbing]

24:14.805 --> 24:18.442
[Band playing that old time religion]

24:52.977 --> 24:54.979
Hello, devil. Welcome to hell.

24:54.979 --> 24:56.480
Hello, Hornbeck.

24:56.480 --> 24:57.982
Hillsboro, Heavenly Hillsboro

24:58.482 --> 25:00.484
The buckle on the bible belt

25:00.484 --> 25:01.986
Come on.

25:02.987 --> 25:04.989
Where are we staying

25:04.989 --> 25:07.491
--we're sharing a room at the mansion house

25:07.491 --> 25:09.994
like everything else
in this town, misnamed

25:09.994 --> 25:11.495
Follow me, and I shall point out

25:11.495 --> 25:14.498
the unplumbed and plumbing-less depths.

25:14.498 --> 25:16.000
Bible
Bible

25:16.500 --> 25:18.502
Hot dogs.
Here y'are. Get your red hots.

25:18.502 --> 25:20.004
That poses a pretty problem.

25:20.004 --> 25:23.007
Which is hungrier-- my stomach or my soul

25:24.008 --> 25:25.009
Hot dog.

25:25.009 --> 25:26.010
Yes, sir.

25:26.010 --> 25:27.511
Tell me, uh, what do you think

25:27.511 --> 25:29.013
of all these monkeyshines

25:29.013 --> 25:31.515
Got no opinion, sir. Opinions are bad for business.

25:31.515 --> 25:32.516
Ah.

25:32.516 --> 25:34.018
Are you a evolutionist

25:34.018 --> 25:36.020
A infidel
A sinner

25:36.520 --> 25:39.023
the worst kind.
I write for a newspaper.

25:39.023 --> 25:40.524
Want a hot dog

25:40.524 --> 25:42.026
No, thanks.

25:42.026 --> 25:44.528
Oh, then you, sir, you must be a man of God.

25:45.029 --> 25:46.530
No, no, no. ulcers

25:51.535 --> 25:53.037
Ladies and gentlemen,

25:53.037 --> 25:58.042
devolution is not a theory but a proven fact.

25:58.042 --> 26:03.047
My friends, man
did not evolve from the ape,

26:03.047 --> 26:08.052
but the ape devolved from man.

26:08.052 --> 26:10.554
Now, you take a look at this creature sitting here.

26:11.055 --> 26:15.059
There before you is an example
of the ungrace

26:15.059 --> 26:18.562
to which man can fall because of his own bestiality.

26:18.562 --> 26:20.064
Look at those beady little brows.

26:20.564 --> 26:22.066
Look at those shifting eyes.

26:22.066 --> 26:23.567
For as sure as the good lord

26:24.068 --> 26:26.070
cast out satan from heavenly glory,

26:26.570 --> 26:30.574
so did he devolve this poor beast from man.

26:30.574 --> 26:33.077
Quit looking at me, will you, son

26:33.077 --> 26:36.080
These are the wages of sin, my friends.

26:36.080 --> 26:37.581
You take a lesson.

26:38.082 --> 26:39.583
Look and beware.

26:40.084 --> 26:42.086
I thank you.

26:42.086 --> 26:45.339
Your contributions will be gratefully received.

26:45.839 --> 26:46.840
Grandpa.

26:47.341 --> 26:48.842
Welcome to Hillsboro, sir.

26:48.842 --> 26:50.344
Have you come to testify

26:50.344 --> 26:52.346
for the prosecution or the defense

26:58.852 --> 26:59.853
You.

27:00.854 --> 27:02.856
You Henry Drummond

27:03.357 --> 27:04.358
Yes, I am.

27:04.358 --> 27:07.361
I'm royce mcHenry, farmer hereabouts.

27:07.861 --> 27:09.363
Nice to know you, Mr. mcHenry.

27:09.363 --> 27:12.866
I want to tell you we're just plain folk down here.

27:12.866 --> 27:14.868
We don't need no outsiders to tell us

27:14.868 --> 27:17.254
how or what to think.

27:17.755 --> 27:20.758
Well, that isn't my mission, Mr. McHenry.

27:20.758 --> 27:23.761
Then why don't you go back where you came from

27:25.262 --> 27:26.263
Hmm.

27:29.767 --> 27:30.768
Pretty hot, aren't they

27:30.768 --> 27:33.270
Their Messiah arrived yesterday.

27:33.771 --> 27:34.772
Look, uh, Drummond,

27:35.272 --> 27:37.274
Why don't you give your ulcers a break and go home

27:37.775 --> 27:39.777
You'll win no victories here.

27:39.777 --> 27:40.778
I've been a lawyer long enough

27:40.778 --> 27:43.280
to know there are no total victories anywhere

27:43.280 --> 27:45.783
Hm. there's only one man in this town who thinks at all,

27:45.783 --> 27:47.284
and he's in jail.

27:47.284 --> 27:49.286
That's why I'm here.

28:05.803 --> 28:08.806
Just, uh, plain folk, 2nd generation.

28:20.934 --> 28:23.437
Mr. Drummond

28:23.437 --> 28:26.440
We're all members of Mr. Cates' homeroom and biology class.

28:26.440 --> 28:28.442
..w-we all like Mr. Cates very much.

28:30.944 --> 28:33.947
And we hope you do right by him.

28:33.947 --> 28:35.949
Well, so do i, son. so do i.

28:50.964 --> 28:51.965
Sarah!

28:51.965 --> 28:54.601
It's good to see you, Henry.

28:55.102 --> 28:58.105
I only wish it were under different
circumstances.

28:58.105 --> 29:01.358
Sarah, you look lovelier than ever

29:01.358 --> 29:03.360
Oh, uh, you know Mr. Hornbeck

29:03.360 --> 29:04.862
How do you do, Mrs. Brady

29:04.862 --> 29:05.863
How do you do, Mr. Hornbeck

29:09.366 --> 29:10.367
Ha ha!

29:11.368 --> 29:12.369
Excuse me.

29:14.872 --> 29:16.874
HHenry! Henry Drummond!

29:17.374 --> 29:18.375
How are you, Henry

29:18.375 --> 29:20.878
Hello, Matt.

29:20.878 --> 29:22.880
I see you've made friends among the younger set.

29:22.880 --> 29:24.882
Yes, youth appeals to me these days.

29:24.882 --> 29:26.383
[Concierge]
Room 206, Mr. Drummond.

29:26.383 --> 29:27.885
Thank you.

29:27.885 --> 29:29.386
Neither of us is getting any younger, eh Henry

29:29.386 --> 29:30.888
Matt, you know what the doctor said

29:30.888 --> 29:33.390
about not overeating in this heat.

29:33.390 --> 29:34.892
Don't worry, mother.

29:34.892 --> 29:36.894
We need strength for the fight ahead.

29:36.894 --> 29:38.395
I'll take up your bags, counselor.

29:38.395 --> 29:39.396
Thank you.

29:39.396 --> 29:42.399
Oh, it's you again, Mr. Hornbeck.

29:42.399 --> 29:44.401
I read your article yesterday.

29:44.401 --> 29:46.904
Very biased reporting, I must say.

29:47.404 --> 29:49.406
Mr. Brady, it's the duty of a newspaper

29:49.907 --> 29:53.410
to comfort the afflicted...
and afflict the comfortable.

29:55.913 --> 29:57.414
I don't like that fellow.

29:57.915 --> 29:59.416
Oh. Henry, I'd like for you to meet

29:59.917 --> 30:01.418
some of the good, uh, people
of Hillsboro.

30:01.418 --> 30:03.420
Mr. Carter, the mayor.

30:03.420 --> 30:04.421
Welcome to Hillsboro.

30:04.421 --> 30:05.923
thank you, your honor.

30:05.923 --> 30:07.424
Prosecuting attorney for this, ah, this district,

30:07.925 --> 30:08.926
Mr. Davenport.

30:08.926 --> 30:10.427
We'll be working together.

30:10.427 --> 30:12.429
Mr. Drummond, sir, let me assure you,

30:12.429 --> 30:14.431
while we may not agree with your ideas,

30:14.431 --> 30:16.433
we respect your right to voice them.

30:16.934 --> 30:18.435
Good boy.

30:18.435 --> 30:20.437
[Brady]
Henry Drummond and I have worked side by side

30:20.437 --> 30:22.940
in a good many battles for the rights of the common folk of this country.

30:23.440 --> 30:24.942
Twice he campaigned for me when I ran
for president.

30:25.442 --> 30:26.443
Isn't that right, Henry

30:26.443 --> 30:27.444
That's right, Matt.

30:27.444 --> 30:28.946
Now, after all these years,

30:28.946 --> 30:32.449
We find ourselves on the opposite
side of an issue.

30:32.950 --> 30:34.952
Well, that's evolution for you.

30:36.453 --> 30:37.454
Good day, gentlemen.

30:37.454 --> 30:39.957
Good day, young gentlemen, and--and thank you.

30:39.957 --> 30:40.958
Sarah.

30:41.458 --> 30:42.960
Good-bye,
Henry.

30:44.461 --> 30:46.830
[Band playing that old time religion]

30:47.331 --> 30:48.832
[Crowd cheering]

31:09.853 --> 31:11.355
[Crowd booing]

31:11.355 --> 31:13.357
[Band playing funeral dirge]

31:21.865 --> 31:22.866
I believe we can desist

31:23.367 --> 31:24.868
with the taking of photographs

31:24.868 --> 31:26.870
for the time being.

31:28.372 --> 31:30.374
Mr. drummond, is the defense ready to proceed

31:30.874 --> 31:33.377
with the selecti on of the next juror

31:33.377 --> 31:34.378
Defense is ready, your honor.

31:34.878 --> 31:37.881
Col. Brady, is the prosecution ready?

31:37.881 --> 31:39.383
Prosecution is ready, your honor.

